plot: After an intense confrontation with Zepeda leaves Bo vulnerable, Winter turns to guardians from Bo's past to protect her once again. As Tate and Winter take risky action to help Bo, revisiting the girl's past reveals surprising information about Channing's history. At Orchestra, Skouras pushes Sean to control his telekinetic abilities, with dangerous results.—Jiilo_Kim

After Bo is shot with a tranquilizer dart, Milton takes them to the closest safe haven he knows. Sarah and Karl MacKenzie had cared for Bo for a time but after an attack by Roman Skouris' head of security, Milton and Bo went on the run. They can't quite believe Milton has returned giving the harrowing and life threatening experience they had the last time. Things only get worse when Bo's condition seems to deteriorate. Milton says she may be going into degrade, a condition of high fever and coma when people like Bo overuse their powers. Tate begins to think that turning her over to Skouris and Orchestra may be their safest bet.—garykmcd
